  "local_port": 56842,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What makeup to wear for red dress?",
  "response": "Choosing the right makeup to complement a red dress can really enhance your overall look. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you choose the perfect makeup for your red dress:\n\n### 1. **Skin Preparation**\n   - **Primer**: Start with a good primer to ensure your makeup lasts longer and looks smooth.\n   - **Foundation**: Use a foundation that matches your skin tone perfectly. Opt for a matte finish if you have oily skin, or a dewy finish for a more radiant look.\n   - **Concealer**: Apply concealer to cover any blemishes or dark circles.\n\n### 2. **Eyes**\n   - **Eyeshadow**: Neutral tones like soft browns, taupes, or champagne shades work well with a red dress. If you want a more dramatic look, you can go for smokey eyes with grays or deep browns.\n   - **Eyeliner**: Use black or dark brown eyeliner to define your eyes. A winged eyeliner can add a touch of elegance.\n   - **Mascara**: Apply mascara to both upper and lower lashes to make your eyes pop.\n\n### 3. **Cheeks**\n   - **Blush**: Choose a blush that complements your skin tone. Peachy or soft pink shades work well with most skin tones and harmonize nicely with red.\n   - **Bronzer/Highlighter**: Use bronzer to add warmth to your face and highlighter to accentuate your cheekbones.\n\n### 4. **Lips**\n   - **Lipstick**: The choice of lipstick depends on the shade of your red dress and the overall look you\u2019re aiming for:\n     - **Nude or Soft Pink**: If you want the focus to be on your dress and eyes, a nude or soft pink lip can be subtle yet chic.\n     - **Bold Red**: If you\u2019re confident with a bold look, you can match your lipstick to your dress. Ensure the undertones of the lipstick and dress are similar (e.g., cool red dress with cool red lipstick).\n     - **Deep Berry or Plum**: For a more sophisticated look, a deep berry or plum shade can work wonderfully.\n\n### 5. **Final Touches**\n   - **Setting Spray**: Finish off with a setting spray to keep your makeup in place.\n   - **Brow Gel**: Groom your eyebrows with a clear or tinted brow gel to frame your face perfectly.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Consider the Occasion**: If you\u2019re attending a formal event, you might want to go for a more polished and sophisticated look. For a casual setting, keep it simple and natural.\n- **Skin Tone**: Consider your skin tone when choosing colors. For example, if you have cool undertones, silver eyeshadows and cool red lipsticks might work better. If you have warm undertones, gold eyeshadows and warmer reds could be more flattering.\n\nRemember, the most important thing is to feel confident and comfortable in your makeup choice. Experiment and find what works best for you and your red dress!",
